{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d62d1008-4327-46c9-ac8c-6732e6e42e2a","content":"Here are the issues I found in this `template.json`:\n\n1. **Missing `identity`** (required) — every template must have a unique `identity` field.\n\n2. **`defaultValue` not in `choices`** (line 10) — `targetFramework` defaults to `\"net7.0\"`, but only `\"net8.0\"` and `\"net9.0\"` are valid choices.\n\n3. **Invalid int default** (line 24) — `maxRetries` has `datatype: \"int\"` but `defaultValue` is `\"abc\"`.\n\n4. **Invalid bool default** (line 19) — `enableLogging` uses `\"yes\"` instead of `\"true\"`/`\"false\"` (the accepted string values for a bool parameter).\n\n5. **`computed` symbol missing `value`** (line 27) — computed symbols require a `value` expression.\n\n6. **`generated` symbol missing `generator`** (line 30) — generated symbols require a `generator` field (e.g., `\"guid\"`, `\"now\"`).\n\n7. **`postActions` entry missing `actionId`** (line 35) — each post action needs an `actionId` GUID (e.g., `\"210D431B-...\"` for dotnet restore).\n\n8. **`shortName` is `\"restore\"`** — while technically valid, this collides with the well-known `dotnet restore` command and will likely confuse users.\n\nWould you like me to fix any or all of these?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"912e8111-b796-4902-b0ea-bb4678700494","outputTokens":358,"requestId":"A7F0:229C6C:1586187:181F360:6A051F54"},"id":"2f805959-3e3d-453f-b47e-dc06f8779205","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:03:24.244Z","parentId":"afde8c40-e487-4f2e-811d-1086f69c2ce6"}
